<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="248" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hale</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 68.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Agency and Consulate General of the
                                        United States of America,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Alexandria, Egypt,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 4, 1866</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On the 29th ultimo John Harrison Surratt
                            was transferred, under a sufficient guard, from the quarantine grounds
                            to the government prison, where he remains in safe confinement.</p>
                        <p>He maintains his demeanor of reticence.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>CHARLES HALE.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon, <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D</hi>. <hi rend="italic">C.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>